main_8420657\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jot1721369395598.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jot1721369395598.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jot1721369395598.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jot1721369395598\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Disable support for non-Gregorian calendars, such as Islamic calendar, Persian calendar,\n\t\tand others, to ensure that <code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>, and\n\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code> works compatibly with versions prior to Uniface\n\t\t10.4.03.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jot1721369395598__p_d141791e1_d141792e1_d141793e1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR</span>\n\t\t\t\t{<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>} | {<code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>}</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jot1721369395598__section_rhc_pfs_2wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499467e72\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"jot1721369395598__ul_lw2_qfs_2wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jot1721369395598__li_d50000e1_d50001e1_d50002e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>—The non-Gregorian calendars are\n\t\t\t\t\tenabled.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jot1721369395598__li_d50003e1_d50004e1_d50005e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>—The non-Gregorian calendars are\n\t\t\t\t\tdisabled.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jot1721369395598__section_lmg_pfs_2wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499467e91\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jot1721369395598__table_d17042e1_d17043e1_d17044e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Any application assignment file </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jot1721369395598__section_bkv_pzl_ccc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499467e137\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code> functions\n\t\t\t\tstarted supporting non-Gregorian calendars from Uniface 10.4.03 onwards. The\n\t\t\t\tapplications developed before this version that use\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$nlsformat=”nlslocale”</code> and a non-Gregorian calendar, may\n\t\t\t\tobserve different behaviors of <code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>, and\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code> functions when migrated to Uniface 10.4.03. The\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR</code> setting is only provided\n\t\t\t\tfor compatibility purposes. </p>\n<p class=\"p\">The default calendars for the locales listed below are non-Gregorian:</p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"jot1721369395598__ul_fdz_4qp_dcc\">\n<li class=\"li\">ar_SA</li>\n<li class=\"li\">ckb_IR</li>\n<li class=\"li\">fa</li>\n<li class=\"li\">fa_AF</li>\n<li class=\"li\">fa_IR</li>\n<li class=\"li\">lrc</li>\n<li class=\"li\">lrc_IR</li>\n<li class=\"li\">mzn</li>\n<li class=\"li\">mzn_IR</li>\n<li class=\"li\">ps</li>\n<li class=\"li\">ps_AF</li>\n<li class=\"li\">th</li>\n<li class=\"li\">th_TH</li>\n<li class=\"li\">uz_Arab</li>\n<li class=\"li\"> uz_Arab_AF</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\">All other locales, unless explicitly set to non-Gregorian, are by default aligned to\n\t\t\t\tthe Gregorian calendar.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"jot1721369395598__note_y2s_1dm_ccc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> <code class=\"ph codeph\">$NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR</code> should be used\n\t\t\t\tonly for the applications developed before Uniface 10.4.03 that use\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$nlsformat=\"nlslocale\"</code> and a non-Gregorian calendar. Using this\n\t\t\t\tsetting is generally discouraged as it limits the local language support.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jot1721369395598__section_yjw_dwp_dcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499467e239\">Example: Using $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, the application developed with 10.4.02 is using\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$nlsformat=\"nlslocale\" </code>and the default calendar for\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">ar_SA</code> is a non-Gregorian calendar.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$nlsformat=\"nlslocale\"</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$nlslocale=\"ar_SA\"</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\">When you migrate to Uniface 10.4.03, the return values of <code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>,\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code> are different. To ensure\n\t\t\t\tcompatibility, configure the compatibility switch as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104jot1721369395598_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"jot1721369395598__codeblock_p22_4wp_dcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SETTINGS]\n$NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR = 1\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdt1718972098664.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$date</a><p>Return the current date or convert the argument to the Date data type.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvg1665702554514.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$datim</a><p>Return the system date and time, or convert the argument to the Datetime data type.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kbw1665702554427.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$clock</a><p>Return the system time or convert the argument to the Time data type.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420657\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420657\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Disable support for non-Gregorian calendars, such as Islamic calendar, Persian calendar, and others, to ensure that $date , $datim , and $clock works compatibly with versions prior to Uniface 10.4.03. $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR { = } { 0 } | { 1 } Arguments 0 —The non-Gregorian calendars are enabled. 1 —The non-Gregorian calendars are disabled. Defaults Assignment file: Any application assignment file Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: 0 Description The $date , $datim , and $clock functions started supporting non-Gregorian calendars from Uniface 10.4.03 onwards. The applications developed before this version that use $nlsformat=”nlslocale” and a non-Gregorian calendar, may observe different behaviors of $date , $datim , and $clock functions when migrated to Uniface 10.4.03. The $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR setting is only provided for compatibility purposes. The default calendars for the locales listed below are non-Gregorian: ar_SA ckb_IR fa fa_AF fa_IR lrc lrc_IR mzn mzn_IR ps ps_AF th th_TH uz_Arab uz_Arab_AF All other locales, unless explicitly set to non-Gregorian, are by default aligned to the Gregorian calendar. Note: $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR should be used only for the applications developed before Uniface 10.4.03 that use $nlsformat=\"nlslocale\" and a non-Gregorian calendar. Using this setting is generally discouraged as it limits the local language support. Example: Using $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR In the following example, the application developed with 10.4.02 is using $nlsformat=\"nlslocale\" and the default calendar for ar_SA is a non-Gregorian calendar. $nlsformat=\"nlslocale\" $nlslocale=\"ar_SA\" When you migrate to Uniface 10.4.03, the return values of $date , $datim , and $clock are different. To ensure compatibility, configure the compatibility switch as follows: Explain this code [SETTINGS] $NLS_DISABLE_NON_GREGORIAN_CALENDAR = 1 Copy Related Links $date Return the current date or convert the argument to the Date data type. $datim Return the system date and time, or convert the argument to the Datetime data type. $clock Return the system time or convert the argument to the Time data type. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}